UC Berkeley, projects should be international and/or comparative in nature, and/or related to the study of languages, and/or involve substantial research outside of the United States.  Fellowship funds are intended to support travel, lodging, and research-related expenditures for graduate students who are conducting research away from campus.  International students enrolled in doctoral programs at UC Berkeley are particularly encouraged to apply.  Preference will be given to students who cannot apply for other sources of funding within the United States.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants', 'Fellowships & Scholarships'], 'audiences': ['Graduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '2/19/2019', 'innovation_stages': [''], 'funding_amount': '$5k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '2-page description', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Turner Fellowship', 'url': 'https://haas.berkeley.edu/financial-aid/evening-weekend-mba/haas-scholarships/continuing-students/', 'resource_email': 'entrepreneurship@haas.berkeley.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'entrepreneurship@haas.berkeley.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'Provided by the generosity of Daniel Turner III,Managing Director of Montreux Equity Partners. A $5,000 annual award will be given to a deserving Evenig- Weekend MBA candidate, who has demonstrated a commitment to an entrereneurial career.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants'], 'audiences': ['Other'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '2/28/2019', 'innovation_stages': ['Startups'], 'funding_amount': '$5k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'PEL/Dumke Award', 'url': 'https://haas.berkeley.edu/financial-aid/full-time-mba/scholarships/', 'resource_email': 'entrepreneurship@haas.berkeley.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'entrepreneurship@haas.berkeley.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'The PEL (Partners in Entrepreneurial Leadership)/Dumke Award is an award for up to $2,500 for continuing students pursuing summer internships with startups that might not be able to compensate interns at market rates. (MBA/MPH students in their second year also qualify for consideration.) Students must have a summer internship at a verifiable startup, not founded by the applying student, received a specific and substantive written job/internship offer, and the internship is for a full-time, summer position for at least 8 weeks in duration.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants', 'Fellowships & Scholarships'], 'audiences': ['Other'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '2/28/2019', 'innovation_stages': ['Startups'], 'funding_amount': '$2.5k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Hansoo Lee Fellowship', 'url': 'https://haas.berkeley.edu/financial-aid/full-time-mba/scholarships/', 'resource_email': 'hansooleefellowship@gmail.com', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'hansooleefellowship@gmail.com', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'Hansoo believed that as a community, the Haas network should encourage entrepreneurship as a full-time internship option by providing students with a stipend and mentors for the summer.  To honor his memory, we have created the Hansoo Lee Fellowship. The Fellowship will provide a stipend and mentorship to help Berkeley-Haas MBA students pursue their venture full-time for their summer internship, as Hansoo did. MBA students will receive: A summer stipend of $5 - $10K Mentorship from Haas alums focused on entrepreneurship', 'types': ['Funding & Grants', 'Fellowships & Scholarships'], 'audiences': ['Graduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '2/28/2019', 'innovation_stages': ['Startups'], 'funding_amount': '$5k-$10k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'John E. Martin Fellowship', 'url': 'https://entrepreneurship.berkeley.edu/fellowships/', 'resource_email': 'entrepreneurship@haas.berkeley.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'entrepreneurship@haas.berkeley.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'The purpose of the fellowship is to provide support for high-achieving MBA, MPH and/or MSW students at UC Berkeley who demonstrate through 1) a student-initiated business/startup or 2) a summer internship commitment to improving the quality of and the access to mental healthcare. Up to two (2) fellowships of $5,000 will be awarded each year.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants'], 'audiences': ['Graduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '2/28/2019', 'innovation_stages': ['Startups'], 'funding_amount': '$5k', 'topics': ['Health & Biotech'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'John L. Simpson Memorial Research Fellowship In International And Comparative Studies', 'url': 'https://iis.berkeley.edu/funding-opportunities/john-l-simpson-memorial-research-fellowship-in-international-and-comparative', 'resource_email': 'iis.grants@berkeley.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'iis.grants@berkeley.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'This research fellowship is a memorial to John L. Simpson to support research in comparative studies that analyzes similarities and differences among societies and states, with respect to social, cultural, political, and economic structures and policies, including patterns of these relationships in global and transnational systems. During his long, illustrious career, Mr. Simpson was awarded the two highest honors bestowed by the University: the Gold Medal for Outstanding Scholar in 1913 and, at Charter Day in 1960, a Doctor of Laws degree for his many years of distinguished public service. This included prominent participation in American relief efforts in Europe during and after World War I, service with a State Department mission to the Allied Control commission in Italy during the later stages of World War II, and early membership in the Belgian-American Educational Foundation, the Council on Foreign Relations in New York, and the Foreign Policy Association. Mr. Simpson served as President of the World Affairs Council of Northern California and was decorated by the French Legion of Honor and the Belgian Order of the Crown. Within the broad category of international/comparative studies, the Institute of International Studies has identified five topics that take priority.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants', 'Fellowships & Scholarships'], 'audiences': ['Graduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '3/18/2019', 'innovation_stages': [''], 'funding_amount': '$15k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '4-page dissertation proposal narrative', 'approva