ncing scholarship in the field of historical sociology, historical demography, or social history.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants', 'Fellowships & Scholarships'], 'audiences': ['Graduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '3/18/2019', 'innovation_stages': [''], 'funding_amount': '$15k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '4-page dissertation proposal narrative', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Berkeley Research On Contemporary India Program (BRCIP) Scholarship', 'url': 'https://iis.berkeley.edu/funding-opportunities/berkeley-research-on-contemporary-india-program-brcip-scholarship', 'resource_email': 'iis.grants@berkeley.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'iis.grants@berkeley.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'The Berkeley Research on Contemporary India Program (BRCIP) fosters undergraduate education and research on India at UC Berkeley.  BRCIP will offer undergraduate scholarships to UC Berkeley students who are conducting research on any area of contemporary India in Spring or Summer 2019.  Research may be conducted independently, in congruence with an honors thesis, or while studying abroad.  After completing their research projects, winners are required to submit a four-page research summary and attend a mini-conference where research will be presented.', 'types': ['Fellowships & Scholarships'], 'audiences': ['Undergraduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '11/13/2018', 'innovation_stages': [''], 'funding_amount': '$2.5k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': 'One-page research proposal', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Undergraduate Conference Travel Grant', 'url': 'https://iis.berkeley.edu/funding-opportunities/undergraduate-conference-travel-grant', 'resource_email': 'iis.grants@berkeley.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'iis.grants@berkeley.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'The Undergraduate Conference Travel Grant supports undergraduate students who plan on traveling to a conference to present a research project, paper, or poster on any topic related to international affairs. Students from all departments are eligible and IIS encourages applications from a wide range of disciplines. The travel grant provides opportunities for individuals to gain valuable educational experience beyond the classroom and recognizes that many UC Berkeley undergraduate students engage in research projects that may require travel to national or international conferences. Grant amounts will depend on the location of  the conference (domestic or international). Students must be registered for the term in which they are planning to attend their conference and be presenting a paper or poster at the  conference.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants'], 'audiences': ['Undergraduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'UC Berkeley', 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '', 'innovation_stages': [''], 'funding_amount': '$300 - $1k', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': 'One-page research description', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Berkeley Cleantech University Prize (CUP)', 'url': 'http://cup.berkeley.edu/', 'resource_email': 'info@beci.berkeley.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'info@beci.berkeley.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'Each fall, student teams from throughout the U.S. will apply to the Berkeley CUP. Selected teams will receive extensive cleantech mentorship, entrepreneurial training, and access to fabrication/prototyping spaces at UC Berkeley. Additionally, selected teams will benefit from the Competition’s dedicated mentors and educators; including world-class professionals from the Haas School of Business’s Cleantech to Market (C2M), Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory’s (LBNL) Cyclotron Road, the American Jobs Project (AJP), the Center for Information Technology Research in the Interest of Society (CITRIS) Foundry, the Sutardja Center for Entrepreneurship and Technology (SCET) and SkyDeck.  After two months of mentorship and training, the selected student teams will compete for the $50,000 Berkeley CUP which will be awarded following a pitch competition in April. Winning teams will advance to the DOE’s Cleantech University Prize National Conference.', 'types': ['Funding & Grants', 'Competitions'], 'audiences': ['Undergraduate Student'], 'population_focuses': [''], 'location': 'Bay Area', 'campuses': [''], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': [''], 'deadline': '', 'innovation_stages': ['Startups'], 'funding_amount': '$50,000', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['BearX.co'], 'notes': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Advance Program', 'url': 'ucd-advance.ucdavis.edu', 'resource_email': 'advance@ucdavis.edu', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'advance@ucdavis.edu', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'UC Davis ADVANCE is an Institutional Transformation grant that began in September of 2012. The program is supported by the National Science Foundation’s ADVANCE Program which aims to increase the participation and advancement of women in academic science and engineering careers. Main initiatives include recruiting talented faculty and staff members that will promote a diverse STEM environment, providing support through training, mentorship, and awards.', 'types': ['Education & Awareness', 'Events', 'Mentoring', 'Networks'], 'audiences': ['Other'], 'population_focuses': ['Women'], 'location': 'California', 'campuses': ['Davis'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': ['Rolling'], 'deadline': '', 'innovation_stages': ['Research-Academia'], 'funding_amount': '', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': [''], 'notes': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Black Engineers Association (BEA)', 'url': 'http://ucdbea.com', 'resource_email': 'UCDBEA.PRESIDENT@GMAIL.COM', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'UCDBEA.PROGRAMSCHAIR@GMAIL.COM', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': "Founded in the 1960's, the Black Engineers Association at the University of California, Davis (UC Davis) is a premier organization for Black students in the STEM fields.  BEA aids in the recruitment, retention and academic success of Black students in the College of Engineering through holding networking events, community service, and inviting guest speakers.", 'types': ['Student Groups', 'Training & Support'], 'audiences': ['Undergraduate Student'], 'population_focuses': ['People of African descent'], 'location': 'California', 'campuses': ['Davis'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': ['Rolling'], 'deadline': '', 'innovation_stages': [''], 'funding_amount': '', 'topics': ['General'], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': [''], 'notes': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}, {'title': 'Society of Women Engineers at UC Davis', 'url': 'http://sweucd.org', 'resource_email': 'swe.ucd@gmail.com', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': 'swe.ucd@gmail.com', 'contact_name': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'The Society of Women Engineers at UC Davis is an active section in the Sacramento-SVS area i